---
import Prose from '../../layouts/Prose.astro';
import QuoteList from '../../components/QuoteList.astro';
import { TECHNIQUES } from '../../lib/techniques';

const t = TECHNIQUES.find((x) => x.slug === 'reading-the-figure')!;
---

<Prose
  title={t.title}
  description={t.description}
  crumbs={[{ name: 'Techniques', href: '/techniques/' }, { name: t.title }]}
  kicker="Technique"
  jsonLd={[{ '@type': 'Article', headline: t.title }]}
>
  <p>
    The separate techniques (houses, witnesses, aspects, company, points) must finally be
    weighed together into one answer. The masters give general rules for this synthesis: when a
    figure is to be called fortunate, how the chart as a whole inclines to good or evil, and the
    order in which the findings are taken. Cattan reckons eight ways a figure is judged good
    or unfortunate; Crowley reduces the whole method to a checklist:
  </p>
  <QuoteList topic="method" />
</Prose>
